{"title":"Sniper rifle","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Sniper_rifle","type":"markdown","data":"| ) [![Sniper rifle.png](/images/3/35/Sniper_rifle.png)](/wiki/File:Sniper_rifle.png) |                                                           |\n| ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Name                                                                                | sniper rifle                                              |\n| Appearance                                                                          | sniper rifle                                              |\n| Damage vs. small                                                                    | 1d2                                                       |\n| Damage vs. large                                                                    | 1d2                                                       |\n| To-hit bonus                                                                        | +4                                                        |\n| Weapon skill                                                                        | [firearms](/wiki/Firearms \"Firearms\")                     |\n| Size                                                                                | [two-handed](/wiki/Two-handed \"Two-handed\")               |\n| Base price                                                                          | 4000 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\") (+10/positive enchant) |\n| Weight                                                                              | [50](/wiki/Weight \"Weight\")                               |\n| Material                                                                            | [iron](/wiki/Iron \"Iron\")                                 |\n\nA sniper rifle is a [firearm](/wiki/Firearm \"Firearm\") introduced in [SLASH'EM](/wiki/SLASH%27EM \"SLASH'EM\"). It is very accurate (+4) and long-ranged (25), but its low rate of fire makes [multishots](/wiki/Multishot \"Multishot\") impossible without [overenchanting](/wiki/Overenchant \"Overenchant\"). It is [two-handed](/wiki/Two-handed \"Two-handed\") and fires [bullets](/wiki/Bullet \"Bullet\").\n\n[ ]\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Rate of fire](#Rate_of_fire)\n- [2 Generation](#Generation)\n- [3 Strategy](#Strategy)\n- [4 Origin](#Origin)\n\n## Rate of fire\n\n| Enchantment | Unskilled/basic | Skilled | Expert        |\n| ----------- | --------------- | ------- | ------------- |\n| +8 or lower | 1               | 1       | 1             |\n| +9          | 1               | 1       | 1d6-4 (min 1) |\n\n## Generation\n\nSniper rifles are not randomly generated.\n\nThere is a 2‚ÅÑ5 chance of one of the [soldiers](/wiki/Soldier \"Soldier\") in [Grund's Stronghold](/wiki/Grund%27s_Stronghold \"Grund's Stronghold\") generating with a +3 sniper rifle.\n\n## Strategy\n\nWhile very accurate, the sniper rifle's low rate of fire and two-handedness make it nearly useless. It does have a higher monetary value than any other firearm at 4000zm, but by the time one reaches Grund's Stronghold, that amount of gold is not likely to be significant. While the sniper rifle does have a longer range than any other firearm, this is unlikely to be factor in most games, since it is rare to be firing at targets halfway across the map.\n\n## Origin\n\nSniper rifles are specialized weapons designed to be accurate at extremely long ranges in the hands of a skilled sharpshooter. Some sniper rifles are derived from ordinary service weapons - usually [assault rifles](/wiki/Assault_rifle \"Assault rifle\") or semi-automatic [rifles](/wiki/Rifle \"Rifle\") - while others are designed from the ground up as specialist weapons. They usually feature accuracy-focused enhancements such as bipods and large scopes.\n\n[![This article may require revision for the next version of SLASH'EM. Click here for more information.](/images/3/38/Se7e7-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article may require revision for the next version of SLASH'EM. Click here for more information.\")\n\n[![This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.](/images/5/5d/Nh343var-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Sniper rifle - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Sniper_rifle\",\"wgTitle\":\"Sniper rifle\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":175259,\"wgRevisionId\":175259,\"wgArticleId\":15251,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Slashem-7E7 articles\",\"SLASH'EM\",\"Variant-343 articles\",\"SLASH'EM firearms\",\"SlashTHEM firearms\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Sniper_rifle\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":15251,\"wgRequestId\":\"35847afe0aadac15554766d3\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[